title: One-day weather delay can’t keep UIW from school-record offensive binge
text:
Photo: Edward A. Ornelas, Staff / San Antonio Express-News Image 1 of / 1 Caption
Close
Image 1 of 1 University of the Incarnate Word's Junior Sessions heads up field between Abilene Christian University's Jabari Butler (left) and Junior Henderson during second half action Sunday Oct. 25, 2015 at Benson Stadium on the UIW campus. UIW won 25-20. University of the Incarnate Word's Junior Sessions heads up field between Abilene Christian University's Jabari Butler (left) and Junior Henderson during second half action Sunday Oct. 25, 2015 at Benson ... more One-day weather delay can’t keep UIW from school-record offensive binge 1 / 1 Back to Gallery UIW coach Larry Kennan ’s long history in pro football has provided him with a natural entry to many recruits because of his vast experience.
“They say with your NFL background, you’ve told a bunch of those guys they would end up playing on Sunday,” Kennan said. “Heck, today they did.”
Kennan’s pronouncement didn’t do justice to his team’s gritty effort. The Cardinals responded to a 24-hour delay in kickoff because of weather conditions with perhaps the best offensive effort in school history.
Junior Sessions’ 15-yard touchdown run with 48 seconds provided the game-winning score to boost the Cardinals to a wild 25-20 victory over Abilene Christian and their fourth comeback victory at Benson Stadium this season.
